Philippine Stocks: Energy Development, JG Summit, PAL Holdings

-- B y   C e c i l i a   Y a p
-- 
2011-03-18T04:43:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-18/philippine-stocks-energy-development-jg-summit-pal-holdings.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual price changes in Philippine trading. Stock symbols
are in parentheses, and prices are as of the noon close.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index rose 0.6 percent to
3,839.88, halting a five-day decline.    Energy Development Corp. (EDC)  , the nation’s largest
geothermal company, climbed 1.9 percent to 6.29 pesos, the
highest since Oct. 7. The company’s net income rose to 4.12
billion pesos ($94 million) last year from 3.31 billion pesos in
2009, the company said in a regulatory filing yesterday. Its
parent  First Gen Corp. (FGEN)  gained 0.8 percent to 12.10 pesos.    JG Summit Holdings Inc. (JGS)  , a company with interests
in airline, food and property, surged 5 percent to 20.45 pesos,
the highest since Dec. 29.    Cebu Air Inc. (CEB) ’s profit more than doubled to 6.92
billion pesos last year from 3.26 billion pesos in 2009, the JG
Summit unit said in a regulatory filing today. The Southeast
Asian nation’s second-largest carrier also declared regular and
special cash dividends totaling 3 pesos a share. Cebu Air
increased 0.7 percent to 85.50 pesos.    PAL Holdings Inc. (PAL)   fell 2 percent to 4.90 pesos.
Its unit Philippine Airlines Inc. may have to review projections
for the fiscal year starting April to consider the effects of  Japan ’s worst earthquake, it said in a statement to the Manila
stock exchange yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cecilia Yap in Manila at   cyap19@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
